# **SECTION M â€” TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE**

### *Services â€¢ Data Model â€¢ Queues â€¢ APIs â€¢ Environments â€¢ Observability*

# --------------------------------------------

Youâ€™re building an **AI OS**, not a toy SaaS.

The architecture has to:

* support **multi-tenant, multi-vertical** growth
* keep **SIVA OS** central, not scattered into random services
* be **stable on Day 1**, but **extensible for Phase 4â€“5**
* fit your current reality (Node/React/Postgres/GCP)
* be understandable by a single founder, but ready for 300 engineers

This section gives the **canonical technical blueprint**.

---

## M.0 High-Level Topology

At 10,000 ft, PremiumRadar consists of:

1. **PremiumRadar Web App** (pageless UI, SIVA surfaces)
2. **PremiumRadar Core API** (multi-tenant app backend)
3. **SIVA OS Service** (reasoning, tools, multi-agent orchestrator)
4. **Jobs & Workers** (queues, async tasks, enrichment)
5. **Data Plane** (Postgres + Vector Store + Object Storage)
6. **AI Provider Layer** (OpenAI, Gemini, Claude, Vertex, SERP, Apollo, etc.)
7. **Observability & Security Layer** (logs, metrics, tracing, WAF)

ASCII:

```text
[ Web App (React/Vite) ]
           â”‚
           â–¼
[ PremiumRadar Core API (Node/Express) ]
           â”‚
     â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”´â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¬â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
     â–¼                     â–¼                â–¼
[SIVA OS Service]   [Jobs/Workers]   [Admin/Super Admin API]
     â”‚                     â”‚                â”‚
     â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¬â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”´â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¬â”€â”€â”€â”˜
             â–¼                          â–¼
       [Data Plane]              [External Providers]
   (Postgres + Vector + S3)   (LLMs, SERP, Apollo, etc.)
```

---

## M.1 Service Breakdown

### M.1.1 PremiumRadar Web App (Frontend)

* Tech: React + Vite + (Tailwind / design system)
* Responsibilities:

  * Pageless AI surfaces (conversation, actions, data, prediction)
  * Auth (JWT/OAuth â†’ Core API)
  * Tenant-aware: loads branding, persona hints, allowed features
  * Strictly â€œdumbâ€ in terms of business logic â€” all intelligence via API

Connects to:

* `/api/*` (Core API)
* `wss://...` (optional real-time updates later)

---

### M.1.2 PremiumRadar Core API (Backend)

* Tech: Node.js / Express / TypeScript
* Single multi-tenant API layer.

Main responsibilities:

* Auth & sessions
* Tenant & user management
* CRUD for:

  * tenants, verticals, sub-verticals, regions
  * campaigns, outreach templates
  * basic packs (Phase 1)
* Orchestrates:

  * SalesContext Engine
  * Intelligence Pack lookup
  * SIVA OS requests
* Writes/reads:

  * leads, opportunities, signals
  * scores, journeys, telemetry
* Exposes:

  * `/api/app/*` for web app
  * `/api/admin/*` for enterprise admins
  * `/api/super-admin/*` for your Super Admin console

This is the **â€œbusiness APIâ€** for the product.

---

### M.1.3 SIVA OS Service

Dedicated service, even if it starts in the same repo.

* Tech: Node/TS orchestrating calls to LLMs
* Responsibilities:

  * SIVA Kernel (context â†’ persona â†’ evidence â†’ tools â†’ reasoning)
  * SalesContext Engine integration (Vertical/SubVertical/Region)
  * Tool routing (enrich, discover, score, outreach)
  * Multi-agent orchestration (CTO AI, CISO AI, etc.)
  * Guardrails enforcement (safety prompts, boundaries, persona governance)
  * Pack-aware reasoning (load FinalPack from Core API/Data Plane)
* Exposes:

  * `/siva/complete`   (core reasoning)
  * `/siva/tools/*`    (tool endpoints)
  * `/siva/agents/*`   (multi-agent actions, internal)
  * `/siva/test/*`     (internal QA)

This must be stateless â†’ all state lives in DB / vector store / cache.

---

### M.1.4 Jobs & Worker Service

Async engine.

* Tech: Node/TS workers
* Queue: GCP Pub/Sub (or Redis-based queue initially)

Responsibilities:

* Long-running or bulk tasks:

  * bulk discovery
  * bulk enrichment
  * scheduled scoring
  * scheduled campaigns
  * pack self-healing batch analysis
  * telemetry aggregation
* Triggered by:

  * Core API
  * SIVA OS (self-healing proposals)
  * Super Admin actions

Workers log results back to DB.

---

### M.1.5 Admin / Super Admin API

Logical subset of Core API with stricter auth:

* `/api/super-admin/*` â†’ only you / ops
* `/api/admin/*` â†’ tenant admins

Responsibilities:

* Super Admin:

  * create tenants
  * attach verticals/sub-verticals
  * create base packs
  * manage APIs & routing rules
  * inspect telemetry & self-healing suggestions
* Tenant Admin:

  * configure campaigns
  * set persona tone within constraints
  * manage users, roles, budgets
  * view analytics

This API **must** respect tenant isolation at DB layer and code layer.

---

## M.2 Data Plane

Three core storage types:

1. **Relational DB (Postgres)** â€” system of record
2. **Vector Store** â€” embeddings for knowledge & RAG
3. **Object Storage** â€” logs, exports, model configs, backups

Youâ€™re already comfortable with Postgres/Supabase; this aligns well.

---

### M.2.1 Core Tables (Simplified Schema)

Not full SQL, but structural blueprint.

#### 1. Tenancy & Users

* `tenants`

  * `id`
  * `name`
  * `type` (enterprise / sme / individual)
  * `region_default`
  * `plan`
  * `api_budget_monthly`
  * `settings_json`
  * `created_at`

* `users`

  * `id`
  * `tenant_id`
  * `email`
  * `role` (super_admin, tenant_admin, manager, rep, viewer)
  * `vertical_default`
  * `sub_vertical_default`
  * `region_default`
  * `persona_prefs_json`
  * `last_login_at`

* `auth_providers` (optional)

  * `user_id`
  * `provider` (password, google, sso)
  * `provider_user_id`

---

#### 2. Vertical / SubVertical / Region Definitions

* `verticals`

  * `id`
  * `key` (banking, insurance, real_estate, recruitment, saas)
  * `label`
  * `meta_json`

* `sub_verticals`

  * `id`
  * `vertical_id`
  * `key` (employee_banking, corporate_banking, mortgage...)
  * `label`
  * `entity_target` (company / individual / family / candidate)
  * `meta_json`

* `regions`

  * `id`
  * `key` (uae_dubai, uae_abu_dhabi, india_chennai, us_ny)
  * `label`
  * `country`
  * `meta_json`

* `tenant_verticals`

  * `tenant_id`
  * `vertical_id`
  * `enabled`

* `tenant_sub_verticals`

  * `tenant_id`
  * `sub_vertical_id`
  * `enabled`
  * `overrides_json` (for persona, compliance, etc.)

---

#### 3. Intelligence Packs

* `intelligence_packs`

  * `id`
  * `scope` (vertical / sub_vertical / region / tenant)
  * `vertical_id`
  * `sub_vertical_id`
  * `region_id`
  * `tenant_id` (nullable for global)
  * `type` (vertical_pack, sub_vertical_pack, region_pack, tenant_override)
  * `pack_json` (internal structure as defined in Section D)
  * `version`
  * `status` (active, draft, deprecated)
  * `created_by`
  * `created_at`
  * `updated_at`

* `pack_versions`

  * `pack_id`
  * `version`
  * `pack_json`
  * `created_at`
  * `change_reason`

---

#### 4. Leads / Opportunities / Signals / Evidence

* `leads`

  * `id`
  * `tenant_id`
  * `user_id`
  * `company_id` (or `person_id` for individual-based verticals)
  * `vertical_id`
  * `sub_vertical_id`
  * `region_id`
  * `status` (new, enriched, scored, outreached, won, lost)
  * `scores_json`
  * `journey_state_json`
  * `created_at`
  * `updated_at`

* `companies`

  * `id`
  * `tenant_id` (nullable for global discovery)
  * `name`
  * `domain`
  * `headcount`
  * `hq_region_id`
  * `meta_json`

* `signals`

  * `id`
  * `company_id` (or `person_id`)
  * `tenant_id`
  * `signal_type` (hiring, funding, expansion, branch_opening...)
  * `source`
  * `payload_json`
  * `confidence`
  * `detected_at`

* `evidence_items`

  * `id`
  * `lead_id` (or `company_id`)
  * `type` (serp, enrichment, historical, tenant_data)
  * `source`
  * `payload_json`
  * `weight`
  * `created_at`

---

#### 5. Outreach & Campaigns

* `campaigns`

  * `id`
  * `tenant_id`
  * `name`
  * `vertical_id`
  * `sub_vertical_id`
  * `region_id`
  * `persona_config_json`
  * `templates_json`
  * `status` (active, paused)

* `outreach_events`

  * `id`
  * `lead_id`
  * `campaign_id`
  * `channel` (email, linkedin, whatsapp)
  * `content_snapshot`
  * `sent_at`
  * `response_status` (no_reply, replied, bounced, positive, negative)
  * `response_at`

---

#### 6. API Usage, Cost & Telemetry

* `api_usage`

  * `id`
  * `tenant_id`
  * `user_id`
  * `provider` (openai, gemini, vertex, serp, apollo)
  * `model_or_endpoint`
  * `tokens_in`
  * `tokens_out`
  * `cost_estimate`
  * `created_at`
  * `meta_json`

* `telemetry_events`

  * `id`
  * `tenant_id`
  * `user_id`
  * `event_type` (journey_step, friction, failure, success, drift_signal)
  * `payload_json`
  * `created_at`

* `self_healing_suggestions`

  * `id`
  * `scope` (pack, persona, scoring, routing)
  * `target_id` (pack_id, vertical_id, etc.)
  * `suggestion_json`
  * `status` (proposed, approved, rejected, applied)
  * `created_at`
  * `approved_by`
  * `applied_at`

---

## M.3 Vector Store & Knowledge

Use a vector DB compatible with GCP stack (e.g., pgvector or a managed vector store).

Key collections:

* `kb_global` (general FAQs, banking norms, generic outreach patterns)
* `kb_vertical_<vertical>` (vertical-specific)
* `kb_tenant_<tenant>` (tenant-specific docs, playbooks, tone docs)
* `kb_packs` (serialized intelligence pack notes for retrieval in prompts)

Each record:

* `id`
* `tenant_id` (nullable)
* `scope` (global/vertical/tenant)
* `embedding`
* `content`
* `meta_json`

SIVA OS uses this in evidence retrieval steps.

---

## M.4 Queues & Background Processing

### Baseline choice: GCP Pub/Sub

Core topics:

* `events.telemetry`
* `jobs.discovery`
* `jobs.enrichment`
* `jobs.scoring`
* `jobs.campaign_send`
* `jobs.self_healing_analysis`

Workers subscribe by type.
Scale horizontally depending on load.

---

## M.5 API Design (External & Internal)

You donâ€™t need REST perfection now. You need **clean contracts** that donâ€™t collapse later.

### M.5.1 App-Facing APIs (Frontend)

Prefix: `/api/app/*`

Examples:

* `POST /api/app/leads/discover`

  * Body: { query, vertical, sub_vertical, region }
  * Calls SCE â†’ SIVA â†’ discovery worker
* `POST /api/app/leads/:id/enrich`
* `POST /api/app/leads/:id/score`
* `POST /api/app/leads/:id/outreach`
* `GET  /api/app/leads/:id`
* `GET  /api/app/dashboard/summary`

---

### M.5.2 Admin APIs

#### Tenant Admin (`/api/admin/*`)

* `GET  /api/admin/campaigns`
* `POST /api/admin/campaigns`
* `GET  /api/admin/analytics/usage`
* `GET  /api/admin/analytics/conversions`

#### Super Admin (`/api/super-admin/*`)

* `POST /api/super-admin/tenants`
* `GET  /api/super-admin/tenants/:id`
* `POST /api/super-admin/intelligence-packs`
* `GET  /api/super-admin/self-healing/suggestions`
* `POST /api/super-admin/self-healing/:id/approve`

---

### M.5.3 SIVA OS Internal APIs

Prefix: `/siva/*`

* `POST /siva/complete`

  * Input: { tenantContext, userContext, salesContext, messages[], toolsAllowed[] }
  * Output: { messages, actions[], reasoning_trace }

* `POST /siva/tool/enrichCompany`

* `POST /siva/tool/scoreOpportunity`

* `POST /siva/tool/generateOutreach`

* `POST /siva/agents/self_healing/analyze`

The **Core API** orchestrates these, SIVA never talks directly to DB.

---

## M.6 Environments & Deployment

### Targets:

* **GCP** as primary cloud
* Containerized services (Cloud Run, GKE later if needed)

Environments:

* `dev` (founder sandbox)
* `staging` (near-production, test tenants)
* `prod` (real customers)

Each env:

* separate DB
* separate pub/sub topics
* separate API keys/secrets

---

## M.7 Observability

Minimum required:

* **Centralized logging** (Stackdriver / OpenTelemetry)
* **Metrics**:

  * SIVA latency
  * API error rate
  * queue lag
  * DB slow queries
* **Tracing**:

  * Request â†’ SIVA â†’ Workers â†’ DB
* **Alarms**:

  * error bursts
  * LLM provider failures
  * API cost ceiling usage
  * self-healing error spikes

---

## M.8 Security & Access Model (High-Level)

* JWT or session-based auth for users
* RBAC:

  * roles (super_admin, tenant_admin, manager, rep, viewer)
  * API route guards
* Tenant isolation:

  * every query filtered by tenant_id
  * enforced at service layer (and optionally via Postgres RLS later)
* API keys:

  * LLM & third-party keys stored in secret manager (GCP Secret Manager)
* WAF:

  * protect from common web threats
* Prompt safety:

  * sanitize user inputs
  * standard safety templates at SIVA layer

---

## M.9 Phase-wise Architecture Evolution

**Phase 1**

* Single repo
* Services may live as modules:

  * `core-api`
  * `siva-os` (same runtime, separate path/namespace)
  * `worker`
* Single Postgres
* Single vector store

**Phase 2â€“3**

* Optionally split:

  * SIVA OS â†’ separate deployment
  * Workers â†’ separate service
* Introduce:

  * dedicated observability stack
  * more advanced caching

**Phase 4â€“5**

* Region-based deployments (EU/US/MEA)
* Multi-region DB / data residency
* Pluggable provider layer / custom models

---

## M.10 Non-Negotiable Architecture Principles

1. **SIVA never queries DB directly**
   â€” everything via Core API & well-defined tools.

2. **No business logic in frontend**
   â€” all intelligence flows from SIVA OS & Packs.

3. **No tenant-specific forks in code**
   â€” everything through Tenancy Engine & Pack overrides.

4. **No hardcoded vertical logic**
   â€” all through SalesContext Engine + Packs.

5. **Everything is observable**
   â€” logs, metrics, telemetry, self-healing traces.

6. **API & Pack contracts are sacred**
   â€” you can evolve implementations, not break contracts.

---
